Begin Reference: Aqua (satellite)
k: null
Text: 'Aqua'
End Reference: Aqua (satellite)
Text: ' satellites. As the total amount of reflected radiation cannot be directly measured by satellite, a '
Begin Reference: mathematical model
End Reference: mathematical model
Text: ' of the BRDF is used to translate a sample set of satellite reflectance measurements into estimates of '
Begin Reference: directional-hemispherical reflectance
End Reference: directional-hemispherical reflectance
Text: ' and bi-hemispherical reflectance.  (e.&nbsp;g.,
.'
Inline Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'NASA']
Text: ')

The Earth's average surface temperature due to its albedo and the '
Begin Reference: greenhouse effect
End Reference: greenhouse effect
Text: ' is currently about 15&nbsp;°C. For the frozen (more reflective) planet the average temperature is below −40&nbsp;°C'
Inline Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'washington']
Text: ' (If only all continents being completely covered by glaciers - the mean temperature is about 0&nbsp;°C'
Inline Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'clim-past']
Text: '). The simulation for (more absorptive) aquaplanet shows the average temperature close to 27&nbsp;°C.'
