k: title
Text: 'The Kuwait oil fires as seen by Landsat '
k: publisher
Text: 'Adsabs.harvard.edu '
k: date
Text: '1991-05-30 '
k: accessdate
Text: '2011-08-19'
End Template: cite web
Close Tag: ref
Text: '

'
Section [1] Aerosol effects
Text: '
'
Begin Reference: Aerosols
End Reference: Aerosols
Text: ' (very fine particles/droplets in the atmosphere) have both direct and indirect effects on the Earth’s radiative balance. The direct (albedo) effect is generally to cool the planet; the indirect effect (the particles act as '
Begin Reference: cloud condensation nuclei
End Reference: cloud condensation nuclei
Text: ' and thereby change '
Begin Reference: cloud
End Reference: cloud
Text: ' properties) is less certain.'
Open Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'girda']
Begin Template: cite web
k: url
Text: 'http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/231.htm#671 '
k: title
Text: 'Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis '
k: publisher
Text: 'Grida.no '
k: date
k: accessdate
Text: '2011-08-19'
k: archiveurl
Text: 'http://web.archive.org/web/20110629175429/http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/231.htm'
k: archivedate
Text: '29 June 2011'
Comment Tag: Added by DASHBot
End Template: cite web
Close Tag: ref
Text: ' As per '
Inline Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'DOMINICK']
Text: ' the effects are:
'
Open Tag: blockquote attributes: []
Text: '
'
Comment Tag:  Aerosol radiative forcing. 
Text: '
* '
ItalicBold: 2
Text: 'Aerosol direct effect.'
ItalicBold: 2
Text: ' Aerosols directly scatter and absorb radiation. The scattering of radiation causes atmospheric cooling, whereas absorption can cause atmospheric warming.
* '
ItalicBold: 2
Text: 'Aerosol indirect effect.'
ItalicBold: 2
Text: ' Aerosols modify the properties of clouds through a subset of the aerosol population called '
Begin Reference: cloud condensation nuclei
End Reference: cloud condensation nuclei
Text: '. Increased nuclei concentrations lead to increased cloud droplet number concentrations, which in turn leads to increased cloud albedo, increased light scattering and radiative cooling ('
ItalicBold: 2
Text: 'first indirect effect'
ItalicBold: 2
Text: '), but also leads to reduced precipitation efficiency and increased lifetime of the cloud ('
ItalicBold: 2
Text: 'second indirect effect'
ItalicBold: 2
Text: ').
'
Close Tag: blockquote
Text: '

'
Section [1] Black carbon
Text: '
Another albedo-related effect on the climate is from black carbon particles. The size of this effect is difficult to quantify: the '
Begin Reference: Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change
End Reference: Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change
Text: ' estimates that the global mean radiative forcing for black carbon aerosols from fossil fuels is +0.2 W m'
Open Tag: sup attributes: []
Text: '−2'
Close Tag: sup
Text: ', with a range +0.1 to +0.4 W m'
Open Tag: sup attributes: []
Text: '−2'
Close Tag: sup
Text: '.'
